# Force consistent LF line endings on checkout, regardless of the
# checking-out machine's core.autocrlf setting. Without this, a fixture
# file like docs/examples/sample_a.txt gets checked out with CRLF on a
# Windows machine with core.autocrlf=true but LF on Linux/macOS CI --
# same git blob, different byte content once read from disk. That's
# invisible until something reads a fixture file's exact bytes (e.g.
# nucle_lang/tests/result_backward_compat.rs's golden-fixture comparison,
# which bakes in a stored file's exact byte count) and compares it
# across machines -- exactly what broke the first time this workspace's
# tests ran on CI instead of only ever locally on Windows.
* text=auto eol=lf
